sectiondef.header: Constructors, destructors, reset and class name methods

description.para: Reset method resets all attribute classes

briefdescription.para: Reset the object, that is 1) removing all childs and 2) resetting all attributes.

detaileddescription.para: The method is virtual, so always call the parent in the method overriding it.

sectiondef.header: Add children to an editorial element.

briefdescription.para: Base method for checking if a child can be added.

detaileddescription.para: The method has to be overridden.

briefdescription.para: Holds the visibility (hidden or visible) for an editorial element.

detaileddescription.para: By default, all editorial elements are visible. However, in an <app>, only one <rdg> is visible at the time. When loading the file, the first <rdg> (or the <lem>) is made visible.

briefdescription.para: This class is a base class for the editorial element containing musical content, for example <rgd> or <add>.

detaileddescription.para: It is not an abstract class but should not be instantiated directly. It can be both a container (in score-based MEI) and a milestone (in page-based MEI).
